text: Trochaclis islandica is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ataphridae. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 1.5 mm and 2.5 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs from Greenland to Norway and in the western part of the Mediterranean Sea. ==References== * Gofas, S.; Le Renard, J.; Bouchet, P. (2001). Mollusca, in: Costello, M.J. et al. (Ed.) (2001). European register of marine species: a check-list of the marine species in Europe and a bibliography of guides to their identification. Collection Patrimoines Naturels, 50: pp. 180–213 ==External links== * Category:Ataphridae Category:Gastropods described in 1989
title: Trochaclis islandica
